    <h1>LET&#x2019;S GET GO&#xAD;ING</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201125/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-25"><time>2020-11-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | LIVING WELL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>When you pull up the app each morn­ing, you will see three grey rings. But as you go about your day, you will no­tice that the grey gives way to colour.</p>
    <p>The red (Move) ring shows how many ac­tive calo­ries you've burnt, the green (Ex­er­cise) ring shows how many min­utes of brisk ac­tiv­ity you've done, and the blue (Stand) ring shows how many times in the day you've stood and moved for at least one minute per hour.</p>
    <p>The ends of the rings inch closer to each other as you be­come more ac­tive. How quickly you com­plete them is based on your per­sonal goals — mine were 350 kilo­calo­ries (Move), 10 min­utes (Ex­er­cise) and 10 min­utes (Stand). These are not the high­est of tar­gets, but it’s a start!</p>

